[[File:Kouka jinja2009-6.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Statue of "Takamitsu-kō and Sarutorahebi" at {{ill|Kōka Shrine (Seki)|ja|高賀神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōka Shrine (Seki)|qq=}}, [[:en:Seki, Gifu|Seki, Gifu]]]] [[File:Mount Koga from Kouka jinja (2015-01-24).JPG|right|thumb|220px|Torii gate of Kōka Shrine with {{ill|Mount Kōga|ja|高賀山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Kōga|qq=}} in the background]]
'''{{ill|Kinpu Shrine (Mino)|ja|金峰神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpu Shrine (Mino)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 御嶽神社}}''' (かねみねじんじゃ<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kinpu Shrine - Gifu Prefecture Shrine Association|url=https://www.gifu-jinjacho.jp/syosai.php?shrno=2481|accessdate=2022-10-30}}</ref>) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Mino, Gifu|Mino, Gifu]], Japan. It is one of the six shrines that form the core of **{{ill|Mount Kōga faith|ja|高賀山信仰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Kōga faith|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}** (高賀山六社).
== Overview == The shrine is one of the **{{ill|Six Shrines of Mount Kōga|ja|高賀山六社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Six Shrines of Mount Kōga|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}**, located along the {{ill|Katachi River|ja|片知川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katachi River|qq=}}, a tributary of the [[:en:Itadori River|Itadori River]], itself a tributary of the [[:en:Nagara River|Nagara River]].
Locals commonly refer to the shrine as "Kanemine Jinja" (かねみねじんじゃ).
== Enshrined Deity == * {{ill|Zaō Gongen|ja|蔵王権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zaō Gongen|qq=}}
The actual sacred objects of worship are said to be statues of: * [[:en:Amitābha|Amitābha]] * {{ill|Ekādaśamukha|ja|十一面観世音菩薩|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ekādaśamukha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 十一面観音}} * [[:en:Kṣitigarbha|Kṣitigarbha]]
Additionally, flanking these statues are images of {{ill|Kongō Zaō|ja|金剛蔵王|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kongō Zaō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 蔵王権現}} and [[:en:Deva (Buddhism)|Tenbu]] deities.
== History == According to shrine tradition, during the **Tenryaku era** (947–957), the **Sarutorahebi** (さるとらへび), a mythical yokai, began terrorizing the local villages. The [[:en:Royal court|Imperial Court (Japan)]] dispatched [[:en:Fujiwara no Takamitsu|Fujiwara no Takamitsu]] to exterminate it.<ref>Another theory suggests the event took place in **Shōhei 3** (933), but this conflicts with Fujiwara no Takamitsu's birth year.</ref>
The first sighting of the Sarutorahebi was at this location, leading to the naming of the area **"Katachi"** (形知), now known as **Katachi** (片知). A shrine was then built in commemoration of the event, originally known as **Katachi Shrine**.
Over time, {{ill|Mount Kōga|ja|高賀山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Kōga|qq=}} gained reverence as a sacred site in [[:en:Mino Province|Mino Province]]. Influenced by [[:en:Shugendō|Shugendō]], the shrine was later renamed **Zaō Gongen Shrine** (蔵王権現社). During the early **Meiji period**, it was renamed **Kinpu Shrine** (金峰神社), likely in reference to [[:en:Kimpusen-ji|Kinpusen-ji]] in [[:en:Yoshino, Nara|Yoshino, Nara]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]].
== The Six Shrines of Mount Kōga == The **Six Shrines of Mount Kōga** are located around Mount Kōga (高賀山), {{ill|Mount Hyōga|ja|瓢ケ岳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Hyōga|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Mount Imabuchi|ja|今渕ケ岳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Imabuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and {{ill|Mount Katachi|ja|片知山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Katachi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Traditionally, ascetics would complete a **one-day pilgrimage** known as **Six Shrine Pilgrimage** (六社めぐり), trekking across mountain ridges.
The six shrines are: * {{ill|Kōka Shrine (Seki)|ja|高賀神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōka Shrine (Seki)|qq=}} ([[:en:Seki, Gifu|Seki, Gifu]]) * {{ill|Nabi Shingū Shrine|ja|那比新宮神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nabi Shingū Shrine|qq=}} ([[:en:Gujō, Gifu|Gujo, Gifu]]) * {{ill|Nabi Hongū Shrine|ja|本宮神社 (郡上市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nabi Hongū Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 那比本宮神社}} (Gujo, Gifu) * {{ill|Hoshimiya Shrine|ja|星宮神社 (郡上市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hoshimiya Shrine|qq=}} (Gujo, Gifu) * {{ill|Taki Shrine (Mino)|ja|瀧神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taki Shrine (Mino)|qq=}} (Mino, Gifu) * **Kinpu Shrine** (Mino, Gifu)
== Access == * **By Bus:** [[:en:Gifu Bus|Gifu Bus]] **Makidani Line** – Get off at **Kanemonbashi (金門橋) Bus Stop**.
