'''{{ill|Kinpu Shrine (Mino)|ja|金峰神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpu Shrine (Mino)|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 御嶽神社|1=Mitake shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11488964}}''' (かねみねじんじゃ<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kinpu Shrine - Gifu Prefecture Shrine Association|url=https://www.gifu-jinjacho.jp/syosai.php?shrno=2481|accessdate=2022-10-30}}</ref>) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|qid=Q845945|lt=Shinto shrine|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|Mino, Gifu|en|Mino, Gifu|qid=Q853835|lt=Mino, Gifu|1=Mino, Gifu}}, Japan. It is one of the six shrines that form the core of **{{ill|Mount Kōga faith|ja|高賀山信仰|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Kōga faith|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}** (高賀山六社).

== Overview ==
The shrine is one of the **{{ill|Six Shrines of Mount Kōga|ja|高賀山六社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Six Shrines of Mount Kōga|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135540766|1=Six Shrines of Mount Kōga}}**, located along the {{ill|Katachi River|ja|片知川|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katachi River|1=Katachi River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q18701005}}, a tributary of the {{ill|Itadori River|en|Itadori River|qid=Q6092348|lt=Itadori River|1=Itadori River}}, itself a tributary of the {{ill|Nagara River|en|Nagara River|qid=Q1194094|lt=Nagara River|1=Nagara River}}.

Locals commonly refer to the shrine as "Kanemine Jinja" (かねみねじんじゃ).

== Enshrined Deity ==
* {{ill|Zaō Gongen|ja|蔵王権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zaō Gongen|qq=}}

The actual sacred objects of worship are said to be statues of:
* {{ill|Amitābha|en|Amitābha|qid=Q236242|lt=Amitābha|1=Amitābha}}
* {{ill|Ekādaśamukha|ja|十一面観世音菩薩|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ekādaśamukha|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 十一面観音|1=Ekādaśamukha|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11404731}}
* {{ill|Kṣitigarbha|en|Kṣitigarbha|qid=Q604687|lt=Kṣitigarbha|1=Kṣitigarbha}}

Additionally, flanking these statues are images of {{ill|Kongō Zaō|ja|金剛蔵王|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kongō Zaō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 蔵王権現|1=Zaō Gongen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q10514059}} and {{ill|Deva (Buddhism)|en|Deva (Buddhism)|qid=Q4089509|lt=Tenbu|1=Deva (Buddhism)}} deities.

== History ==
According to shrine tradition, during the **Tenryaku era** (947–957), the **Sarutorahebi** (さるとらへび), a mythical yokai, began terrorizing the local villages. The {{ill|Royal court|en|Royal court|qid=Q1134237|lt=Imperial Court (Japan)|1=Royal court}} dispatched {{ill|Fujiwara no Takamitsu|en|Fujiwara no Takamitsu|qid=Q3071886|lt=Fujiwara no Takamitsu|1=Fujiwara no Takamitsu}} to exterminate it.<ref>Another theory suggests the event took place in **Shōhei 3** (933), but this conflicts with Fujiwara no Takamitsu's birth year.</ref> 

The first sighting of the Sarutorahebi was at this location, leading to the naming of the area **"Katachi"** (形知), now known as **Katachi** (片知). A shrine was then built in commemoration of the event, originally known as **Katachi Shrine**. 

Over time, {{ill|Mount Kōga|ja|高賀山|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Kōga|1=Mount Koga|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11672865}} gained reverence as a sacred site in {{ill|Mino Province|en|Mino Province|qid=Q864156|lt=Mino Province|1=Mino Province}}. Influenced by {{ill|Shugendō|en|Shugendō|qid=Q1483875|lt=Shugendō|1=Shugendō}}, the shrine was later renamed **Zaō Gongen Shrine** (蔵王権現社). During the early **Meiji period**, it was renamed **Kinpu Shrine** (金峰神社), likely in reference to {{ill|Kimpusen-ji|en|Kimpusen-ji|qid=Q1741668|lt=Kinpusen-ji|1=Kimpusen-ji}} in {{ill|Yoshino, Nara|en|Yoshino, Nara|qid=Q1203731|lt=Yoshino, Nara|1=Yoshino, Nara}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|en|Nara Prefecture|qid=Q131287|lt=Nara Prefecture|1=Nara Prefecture}}.

== The Six Shrines of Mount Kōga ==
The **Six Shrines of Mount Kōga** are located around Mount Kōga (高賀山), {{ill|Mount Hyōga|ja|瓢ケ岳|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Hyōga|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Mount Imabuchi|ja|今渕ケ岳|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Imabuchi|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and {{ill|Mount Katachi|ja|片知山|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Katachi|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Traditionally, ascetics would complete a **one-day pilgrimage** known as **Six Shrine Pilgrimage** (六社めぐり), trekking across mountain ridges.

The six shrines are:
* {{ill|Kōka Shrine (Seki)|ja|高賀神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōka Shrine (Seki)|1=Kōka Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11672867}} ({{ill|Seki, Gifu|en|Seki, Gifu|qid=Q860647|lt=Seki, Gifu|1=Seki, Gifu}})
* {{ill|Nabi Shingū Shrine|ja|那比新宮神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nabi Shingū Shrine|1=Nabi Shingū Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11642751}} ({{ill|Gujō, Gifu|en|Gujō, Gifu|qid=Q857243|lt=Gujo, Gifu|1=Gujō, Gifu}})
* {{ill|Nabi Hongū Shrine|ja|本宮神社 (郡上市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nabi Hongū Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 那比本宮神社|1=Nabi Hongū Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q28684739}} (Gujo, Gifu)
* {{ill|Hoshimiya Shrine|ja|星宮神社 (郡上市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hoshimiya Shrine|qq=}} (Gujo, Gifu)
* {{ill|Taki Shrine (Mino)|ja|瀧神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taki Shrine (Mino)|1=Taki Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11566355}} (Mino, Gifu)
* **Kinpu Shrine** (Mino, Gifu)

== Access ==
* **By Bus:** {{ill|Gifu Bus|en|Gifu Bus|qid=Q5560101|lt=Gifu Bus|1=Gifu Bus}} **Makidani Line** – Get off at **Kanemonbashi (金門橋) Bus Stop**.

